text.section:
The Board of Trustees shall adopt rules and regulations that specify with respect to classified employees:
The manner of establishing appropriate collective bargaining units and of designating exclusive bargaining representatives;
The rights of the employer, the employees, and the exclusive bargaining representative;
The procedure for negotiating a collective bargaining agreement with respect to wages, hours, and working conditions and the manner for resolving any impasse;
The right of the exclusive bargaining representative to a checkoff of union dues;
The designation of unfair labor practices and remedies for them;
The definition of a grievance and the procedure for resolving grievances, which may include binding arbitration of grievances; and
Any other matter necessary to carry out the purposes of this section.
